template.description: add flag for onramp for whether virus scan should be done
template.name: SDD-RP-SecureZone-v4.6

labels.label: Put a json of data file attributes into the awaiting approval queue. A command line approval script (/scripts/approve_import.sh <filename>)will trigger the flow to continue.
Save the trigger email fields so that when the data files arrive in the secure area the fields can be added as attributes

Monitor a folder in the secure zone for manual approvals for processing data files that are already in the secure zone Assumption is that datafile is a zip file that is either unencrypted (default) or gpg encrypted. To approve a file, in the monitored folder, run <scripts folder>/approve_import_rz_onramp.sh <filename> You may want to create a local bash file with the above command e.g., /scripts/approve_import_onramp_rz.sh "$@" You can specify GPG decryption when approving the file via the -d flag You can enable virus scanning via the -v flag
Decrypt the trigger email and extract out the fields of interest
Generate metadata for "data" folder. Save metadata to "metadata" folder.
Unzips and decrypts. Saves to "data" folder. Handles 4 cases: 1) GPG encrypted zip/7z 2) Unencrypted zip/7z with GPG encrypted files in it 3) AES encyrpted zip/7z with passphrase 4) Unenrypted zip/7z
Generate the summary report. Save a copy in the intake folder and notify stakeholders that report is ready for review.
When summary reports are approved (by moving them into the approved reports folder), send an email to stakeholders. Approved metadata is sent to the staging zone for storage.
When the data files arrive, we need to add the information (e.g., pass phrase) from the trigger email to them as attributes. The Notify processor does this.
Save the files to an intake folder

Monitor "approved" folder. Get manually approved json files. To do a manual approval, in the monitored folder, run <scripts folder>/approve_import.sh <filename> Collect the approver and approval time so it can be incorporated into the data file's metadata. Trigger the flow to continue for the approved data file.

Remove attributes except DataFileName then delete the contents of the file (to minimize what we send to the staging zone). This flow will go to the staging area and trigger the flow of data files to the secure zone.
Process approval info json file which was automatically created by bash script
